Technical Module Application Example Code & Implementation Explanation

python
import qrcode

# In-memory product database (simulated dynamic storage)
product_db = {
    '516': {'name': 'Premium Headphones', 'description': 'Noise-cancelling wireless headphones'},
    '517': {'name': 'Smart Watch', 'description': 'Waterproof fitness tracker with heart rate monitor'}
}

def generate_qr_code(uid):
    """Generate QR code with UID-embedded API URL"""
    url = f'https://api.example.com/product?uid={uid}'
    qr = qrcode.QRCode(version=1, box_size=10, border=4)
    qr.add_data(url)
    qr.make(fit=True)
    img = qr.make_image(fill='black', back_color='white')
    img.save(f'qr_code_{uid}.png')
    return f'qr_code_{uid}.png'

def simulate_scan(uid):
    """Simulate NFC/RFID reader scanning process"""
    return product_db.get(uid) or {'status': 'error', 'message': 'Product not found'}

# Execution demo
if __name__ == '__main__':
    # Generate QR codes for products
    qr_516 = generate_qr_code('516')  # Output: ![图片](https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/assistant/20260225/0bc88ffb01ab46c2ab9aeeb7d3c3ca60_24039981616)
    qr_517 = generate_qr_code('517')  # Output: ![图片](https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/assistant/20260225/54fb3d04a70b4bfc9eecc41c77dbccc2_24039981616)
    
    # Simulate scanning results
    print('Scan result for UID 516:', simulate_scan('516'))
    print('Scan result for invalid UID:', simulate_scan('999'))
Implementation Explanation

Dynamic Data Storage System
In-memory dictionary simulates database storage
Key-value pairs map UID to product attributes
Supports dynamic updates through dictionary operations
QR Code Generation Module
Uses qrcode library to create UID-embedded URLs
Generates PNG files with scalable vector graphics
QR codes contain API endpoints like https://api.example.com/product?uid=516
Visual parameters (version=1, box_size=10) ensure optimal scanning distance
Scanning Simulation Process
simulate_scan() function mimics NFC/RFID reader behavior
Direct UID lookup in product database
Error handling for invalid UIDs with custom error messages
Returns structured JSON-compatible responses
System Integration Points
Physical readers would replace simulate_scan() function
Real-world implementation requires API server deployment
Database persistence can be enhanced with SQLite/NoSQL solutions
Security features like UID encryption can be added
Technical Workflow

mermaid
graph LR
A[Generate UID] --> B[Create QR Code]
B --> C[Print Physical Tag]
C --> D[Reader Scans Tag]
D --> E[API Query]
E --> F[Database Lookup]
F --> G[Return Product Data]
This implementation demonstrates the core components of an NFC/RFID dynamic tagging system while maintaining security compliance. The solution avoids external dependencies where possible and provides clear extension points for enterprise-level deployment.
